After some delays, the ANC’s Gauteng Elective Conference is finally underway. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - After some delays, the ANC’s Gauteng Elective Conference is finally underway. Panyaza Lesufi -- who is vying for the position of chairperson -- says the conference will be a success and that it is vital to appoint a leader that will take the province forward. Lesufi says ANC leaders need to always put the party first. READ: ANC Gauteng elective conference to begin on Thursday Lebogang Maile is also a contender for the position of chairperson. Meanwhile, outgoing provincial chair, David Makhura, said the ANC in Gauteng will emerge united. Makhura says he's confident the new leadership that's set to be elected this weekend will move the province forward. Outgoing provincial chair David Makhura says the ANC in Gauteng will emerge united. Makhura says he's confident the new leadership that's set to be elected this weekend will move the province forward. He was delivering a political report at the Provincial Conference in Benoni. #DStv403 All eyes are on the Gauteng ANC Provincial Executive, on Friday afternoon. Courtesy of #DStv403